Entering college about eight years ago, my parents told me that this is the time of your life where you decide who you will become. Quite a scary thought for someone that liked little bits and pieces of each subject I learned in school. I decided to major in Chemistry, something I did moderately well in high school and could lead to the path of becoming a pharmacist, the phrase a lot of my peers around me mentioned more so because of their parents then because of themselves. Nevertheless, my experience in college life led me to find genuine interest in Computer as well as Web Development. I have posted my projects and several coursework on portfolio page.
